Anonymous Sat 11 Jan 2020 00:57:43 No.27677890 Report
Quoted By: >>27678572
>>27674166
My dude... If you're looking to build something you can take back apart, you're probably going to want to use carriage bolts. Whether you use them or hex heads, you're going to want to do through holes and either use a nut and washer on the back of the joint or use some sort of tap in anchor (a metal insert that the bolt will thread into... the recommended hole size and depth will be in the instructions). If it's plywood/NDF/MDF, do NOT use tap-in anchors. Just use a nut/washer (and possibly a scab plate between the wood and the washers if it's a heavily loaded / cyclically loaded joint). For the through hole diameter, just use the shank of the bolt (the diameter of the unthreaded section, not the head).

Do NOT use wood screws or lags unless it's only getting assembled once.
